01:46.589 --> 01:47.856
Look!

01:47.924 --> 01:49.791
There goes our car.

01:49.859 --> 01:51.860
Is that a parade float?

01:51.928 --> 01:54.096
It's not a parade float.

01:54.163 --> 01:57.399
It's my parade float.

01:59.535 --> 02:01.470
- Is it made
out of paper mâché?

02:01.537 --> 02:04.206
Papier-mâché, yes.

02:04.274 --> 02:05.707
- What will happen
when it gets wet?

02:05.775 --> 02:08.276
It's going to get wet?

02:18.154 --> 02:20.889
Turn off the water!
Turn off the water!

02:20.957 --> 02:22.924
Turn off the water!

02:37.440 --> 02:41.243
Turn off the water!
Turn off the water!

02:49.085 --> 02:51.119
Aah! Eek! Ooh!

03:48.945 --> 03:51.747
My eye! My eye!

03:51.814 --> 03:54.249
Oh, my eye!
- Daffy? Don't move!

03:54.317 --> 03:56.718
I'm getting the first aid kit!
- Oh, no!

03:59.455 --> 04:00.856
Let me see your eye!

04:00.923 --> 04:02.858
It's all that's left--

04:02.925 --> 04:06.628
My beautiful parade float
is gone!

04:06.696 --> 04:10.532
We--we never even got to be
in a parade!

04:14.637 --> 04:16.071
You going to be ok?

04:17.173 --> 04:18.540
He'll be ok.

04:18.608 --> 04:20.976
Probably just needs
a little time.

05:00.249 --> 05:02.918
Maybe that's enough time.

05:04.687 --> 05:06.555
Daffy?

05:06.622 --> 05:09.191
Bugs! I knew it!

05:09.258 --> 05:11.793
I knew
you'd come through for me.

05:11.861 --> 05:14.463
I knew if I stayed
in here long enough

05:14.530 --> 05:16.364
And sobbed loud enough,

05:16.432 --> 05:18.700
You'd make me
another parade float.

05:18.768 --> 05:21.570
It wasn't easy. There were
days when I wanted to give up,

05:21.637 --> 05:24.072
When I wanted to come out of
my room, maybe take a shower.

05:24.140 --> 05:27.142
But I persevered.
I stayed in my room,

05:27.210 --> 05:29.044
And I sobbed even louder,

05:29.111 --> 05:32.881
Because I knew that you needed
that time and that motivation,

05:32.949 --> 05:36.985
And I was right.
Thank you, brother.

05:37.053 --> 05:40.155
So, where is it? Where's my
new, beautiful parade float?

05:40.223 --> 05:42.390
- I didn't make you
a parade float.

05:53.769 --> 05:56.872
- I'm fine.
I'm disappointed, but I'm fine.

05:56.939 --> 05:59.674
- Why can't you just drive
a normal car?

05:59.742 --> 06:02.777
- Normal cars are
for normal people.

06:02.845 --> 06:04.246
I'm not normal!

06:04.313 --> 06:05.847
I'll give you that.

06:05.915 --> 06:07.782
You're my best friend.

06:07.850 --> 06:10.151
You know me better than anyone.

06:10.219 --> 06:12.921
You see
what a horrible person I am.

06:12.989 --> 06:15.690
That's why I have
to drive a parade float--

06:15.758 --> 06:19.461
To distract the rest of
the world from seeing it!

06:19.529 --> 06:22.697
- You're going to need something
better than a parade float.

06:22.765 --> 06:25.467
Better than a parade float?

06:25.535 --> 06:28.537
Better than a parade float...

06:30.773 --> 06:32.374
I'll take it.

06:37.880 --> 06:40.082
Not since my parade float

06:40.149 --> 06:46.121
Have I felt that a vehicle
so expressed my essence.

06:46.189 --> 06:47.489
How much?

06:47.557 --> 06:49.124
375,000.

06:49.192 --> 06:51.793
- Dollars?
- Yes.

06:51.861 --> 06:55.931
American dollars?

06:55.998 --> 06:59.601
- I'm not giving you $375,000
for a yacht.

06:59.669 --> 07:01.203
But you're my best friend.

07:01.270 --> 07:03.004
That's what best friends do.

07:03.072 --> 07:05.407
No, they don't.

07:07.510 --> 07:11.847
- Fair enough.
Will you give me $375,000,

07:11.914 --> 07:15.484
Which I will donate
to the charity of my choice?

07:17.019 --> 07:21.456
- Daffy, no one's going
to give you $375,000.

07:21.524 --> 07:24.993
- of course
I'll give you $375,000.

07:25.061 --> 07:26.695
- I knew I could count on you,
Porky.

07:26.763 --> 07:30.198
- You poor thing. I didn't
even know you were sick.

07:30.266 --> 07:31.833
But when's the operation?

07:31.901 --> 07:33.969
- Tonight,
so let's wrap this up.

07:34.036 --> 07:36.538
- Can I ask why you didn't go
to Bugs for the money?

07:36.606 --> 07:38.807
- Because
you're my best friend.

07:38.875 --> 07:41.777
I know that
I can ask you for anything,

07:41.844 --> 07:45.380
Just as you know that
you can ask me for anything.

07:47.583 --> 07:49.117
- Could you turn on
that lamp for me?

07:49.185 --> 07:51.019
I can't see the combination.

07:52.355 --> 07:53.922
Do it yourself.

08:00.596 --> 08:02.597
Here you go.

08:12.408 --> 08:14.810
This is only $350,000.

08:14.877 --> 08:16.578
But it's all I have.

08:16.646 --> 08:20.081
- Porky, you are making this
very hard for me.

08:20.149 --> 08:23.885
Do you think I like having to
come to my best friend for money?

08:23.953 --> 08:26.555
Can you imagine
what this is like for me,

08:26.622 --> 08:29.090
How awkward this is?

08:29.158 --> 08:31.726
What's that
in the back of the safe?

08:31.794 --> 08:34.929
A gold watch?

08:34.996 --> 08:37.631
- But that was
my great-grandfather's.

08:37.700 --> 08:41.403
- "randall pig"?
It's engraved?

08:41.470 --> 08:43.638
That's going to kill
its resale value.

08:43.706 --> 08:45.006
I'm going to need
more than this.

08:45.074 --> 08:46.107
Give me your debit card.

08:46.175 --> 08:48.109
- But that's the money
I live on.

08:48.177 --> 08:50.178
- Porky, I can't sit here
and argue with you.

08:50.246 --> 08:52.147
The surgery's, like,
in 10 minutes.

08:52.215 --> 08:54.749
- You're right.
Take the debit card.

08:54.817 --> 08:57.752
"take the debit card" what?

08:57.820 --> 09:00.689
- Take the debit card,
please?

09:00.756 --> 09:04.659
- Fine. As a favor to you,
I'll take the debit card.

09:04.727 --> 09:08.330
What is this, wool? All right.
I guess I'll take the coat, too.

09:13.302 --> 09:16.605
Maybe I can get
a couple of bits for this.

09:16.672 --> 09:18.273
feel better!

09:18.341 --> 09:21.743
Wait a second.
Now, how am I going to live?

09:24.614 --> 09:26.414
Whoo-hoo!

09:26.482 --> 09:30.952
I'm free!
I've never felt so alive!

09:31.020 --> 09:34.422
The high seas,
the wind in my hair,

09:34.490 --> 09:36.658
The salt on my skin!

09:36.726 --> 09:38.760
I am a sailor!

09:38.828 --> 09:41.296
I am sailing!

09:41.364 --> 09:45.734
What an unbelievable rush!
Whoo-hoo!

09:56.312 --> 09:57.846
Porky?

09:57.914 --> 09:59.180
What are you doing?

09:59.248 --> 10:02.350
Eating garbage.

10:02.418 --> 10:04.452
- Is that something
you've always done,

10:04.520 --> 10:06.421
Or is that a new thing?

10:06.489 --> 10:09.024
- Are you going
to finish that?

10:13.696 --> 10:16.331
- I tried calling you, but
your phone's been disconnected.

10:16.399 --> 10:19.367
Why is it so dark in here,
and cold?

10:19.435 --> 10:21.636
- I couldn't pay my bills.
- Why not?

10:21.704 --> 10:23.405
I gave all my money to Daffy.

10:23.472 --> 10:25.774
- Why would you give
all your money to Daffy?

10:25.841 --> 10:29.344
- For his kidney transplant.
Do you know how he's doing?

10:29.412 --> 10:32.013
Let's go find out.

10:38.020 --> 10:39.921
Ahh.

10:39.989 --> 10:43.825
I should have bought a yacht
with Porky's money years ago.

10:45.895 --> 10:47.595
Nice boat.

10:47.663 --> 10:49.230
- She's a real beauty,
isn't she?

10:49.298 --> 10:51.599
The Queen of the Ocean.
That's why I named her that.

10:51.667 --> 10:54.636
A fitting name for the successor
to my parade float.

10:54.704 --> 10:57.973
Which,y the way, which was
also named "Queen of the Ocean."

10:58.040 --> 11:00.709
- How's the kidney?
- Kidney?

11:00.776 --> 11:03.645
Oh, I just told Porky that so he'd
give me the money for the yacht.

11:18.127 --> 11:20.061
Mmm. Good shrimp.

