♪ our friendship
will never end ♪

12:00.836 --> 12:02.904
♪ if we were divers,
we'd get the bends ♪

12:02.972 --> 12:04.906
♪ we're such deep friends ♪

12:04.974 --> 12:06.674
♪ sometimes, we disagree ♪

12:06.742 --> 12:11.012
♪ we must monitor our chi
and realign our energy ♪

12:11.080 --> 12:13.348
♪ we are best friends ♪

12:29.331 --> 12:30.765
- Dance break!
- Splendid! After you!

12:30.833 --> 12:32.967
- Oh, no, I insist,
you're a much better dancer.

12:33.035 --> 12:34.536
- Oh, you flatter me.
- Not at all.

12:34.603 --> 12:36.771
- Ok, dance break's over.
- Never mind.

12:36.839 --> 12:38.773
- ♪ you like toning up
your lats ♪

12:38.841 --> 12:40.642
- ♪ I like wearing
my new spats ♪

12:40.709 --> 12:42.343
- ♪ it don't get
no better than that ♪

12:42.411 --> 12:44.612
- ♪ when you're best friends,
you're best friends ♪

12:44.680 --> 12:46.481
- ♪ you like gray
and I like beige ♪

12:46.549 --> 12:48.483
- ♪ luckily, for us,
there's graige ♪

12:48.551 --> 12:50.552
- ♪ which is
a lovely combina-tion ♪

12:50.619 --> 12:52.887
♪ of gray and beige ♪

12:52.955 --> 12:54.489
♪ you like designer boots ♪

12:54.557 --> 12:56.458
- ♪ I like velvet
warm-up suits ♪

12:56.525 --> 12:58.493
- ♪ in that way,
we're in cahoots ♪

12:58.561 --> 13:00.628
- ♪ we're best friends,
we're best friends ♪

13:00.696 --> 13:02.464
- ♪ you like red,
and I like blue ♪

13:02.531 --> 13:04.632
♪ you like me,
and I like you ♪

13:04.700 --> 13:07.635
♪ there's nothing else to do
but be best friends ♪

13:07.703 --> 13:09.204
♪ be best friends ♪

13:14.944 --> 13:17.278
♪ we are best friends ♪

13:30.800 --> 13:32.167
Yeow!

13:36.206 --> 13:37.773
Ooh...

13:37.841 --> 13:40.543
wait!

13:40.610 --> 13:42.611
That's a Tiffany lamp.

13:42.679 --> 13:44.613
- that you bought
with my money!

13:45.949 --> 13:47.449
Aah!

13:47.517 --> 13:50.085
How could you lie to me?

13:50.153 --> 13:52.922
- I'm sorry. I thought if I
told you what the money was for,

13:52.989 --> 13:54.390
You wouldn't give it to me.

13:54.457 --> 13:56.492
I wouldn't have!

13:56.560 --> 13:58.561
You just proved my point.

13:58.628 --> 14:00.729
How am I the bad guy here?

14:07.170 --> 14:10.172
Ok. I've had enough.

14:10.240 --> 14:12.007
Well, maybe just one more.

14:15.345 --> 14:16.745
All right. Break it up.

14:17.914 --> 14:19.248
- Here's what
we're going to do.

14:19.316 --> 14:20.950
Daffy, you're going
to sell this thing

14:21.017 --> 14:22.585
And give Porky
his money back.

14:22.652 --> 14:25.721
- Are you crazy?
I already lost my parade float!

14:25.789 --> 14:27.690
I'm not about
to lose my yacht.

14:32.829 --> 14:34.930
- Well, you're about
to lose a friend.

14:34.998 --> 14:37.333
- Yeah, but those are easy
to get when you have a yacht.

14:37.400 --> 14:40.002
Uh, guys?

14:40.937 --> 14:42.237
Where's the dock?

14:42.305 --> 14:44.773
But that's impossible.

14:44.841 --> 14:46.342
I tied a shank knot
to this cleat,

14:46.409 --> 14:48.277
Tied a sheepshead knot here,

14:48.345 --> 14:50.112
A double rolling hitch here,

14:50.180 --> 14:52.448
A simple,
yet elegant bow here.

14:52.515 --> 14:54.717
And a square knot here.
- Uh-huh.

14:54.784 --> 14:57.219
And what kind of knot
did you tie to the dock?

15:09.699 --> 15:11.734
what are we going to do?

15:11.801 --> 15:14.803
We're stranded
in the middle of the ocean!

15:14.871 --> 15:18.307
I always knew
I'd die this way!

15:18.375 --> 15:20.242
- All right.
Let's not panic.

15:20.310 --> 15:24.013
We'll just put up the sail
and sail back.

15:28.051 --> 15:29.618
Where's the sail?

15:29.686 --> 15:31.553
I didn't get one.

15:31.621 --> 15:32.721
What?

15:32.789 --> 15:33.956
I didn't have enough money.

15:34.024 --> 15:36.225
I was forced to choose
between a sail

15:36.292 --> 15:37.826
And this jacuzzi.

15:37.894 --> 15:40.062
So if anyone's to blame,
it's Porky.

15:40.130 --> 15:43.899
- I gave you everything I had.
I'm completely broke!

15:43.967 --> 15:47.036
- The fact that you're not more
financially successful is not my fault.

15:48.972 --> 15:52.141
- What? Is it me?
It's him, right?

15:52.208 --> 15:54.910
- We'll just radio
the coast guard for help.

15:54.978 --> 15:56.912
- Nope. No radio.
- What?

15:56.980 --> 15:58.347
There wasn't enough money,

15:58.415 --> 16:00.349
Not after I got
the second jacuzzi.

16:02.018 --> 16:03.385
I have an idea.

16:03.453 --> 16:06.455
Let's all take a long, hot soak
in the jacuzzi.

16:06.523 --> 16:09.091
It will relax us,
which will allow us

16:09.159 --> 16:12.294
To think of a way
out of our predicament.

16:12.362 --> 16:15.297
I'll take the master jacuzzi.
You two take that one.

16:17.434 --> 16:20.736
Ha. Ah! Ooh!

16:20.804 --> 16:22.938
Ahh. Ahh.

16:26.710 --> 16:30.079
I think I have our answer.

16:30.146 --> 16:32.614
Porky should swim back
and get help.

16:32.682 --> 16:34.249
Off you go, Porky.
- Hey, what are you doing?

16:34.317 --> 16:35.984
Stop! What do you think
you're doing?

16:36.052 --> 16:38.187
No one's swimming anywhere.

16:38.254 --> 16:39.988
We're sailing back.

16:42.726 --> 16:44.026
Where'd you get a sail?

16:44.094 --> 16:45.728
It's your bedsheets.

16:45.795 --> 16:49.531
- What? Those are 1,500
thread count egyptian cotton!

16:51.134 --> 16:54.536
Do you know
how much these sheets cost?

16:54.604 --> 16:56.205
More than lifejackets!

16:56.272 --> 16:58.974
That's why there are
no lifejackets on board!

16:59.042 --> 17:01.376
Well, that, and they make you
look stupid.

17:05.682 --> 17:07.148
Aah!

17:12.122 --> 17:15.924
- He's unconscious!
What should we do?

17:28.772 --> 17:31.340
- Psst. Porky.
Untie me.

17:31.407 --> 17:34.710
- I can't.
I'm under direct orders not to.

17:34.778 --> 17:38.013
- You know, Porky, being out
here in the middle of the ocean

17:38.081 --> 17:41.150
Has really made me
reevaluate some things.

17:41.217 --> 17:44.953
I see now that it's not money
or things that matter.

17:45.021 --> 17:48.023
It's friends--
best friends.

17:48.091 --> 17:52.327
And you, Porky Pig,
you are my best friend.

17:52.395 --> 17:54.229
Do you really mean it?

17:54.297 --> 17:56.965
Have you ever known me to lie?

17:57.033 --> 18:00.602
- Yes. You lied about
needing a kidney transplant.

18:00.670 --> 18:02.204
That's in the past.

18:02.272 --> 18:04.540
Now, please, untie me

18:04.607 --> 18:09.178
So I can give my best friend
a great big hug.

18:09.245 --> 18:11.880
You won't regret this.

18:14.083 --> 18:16.385
now, go swim and get help.

18:16.452 --> 18:18.520
Aah!

18:18.588 --> 18:20.789
Porky!

18:24.360 --> 18:26.829
- Well,
I guess it's just me now,

18:26.896 --> 18:29.064
All alone on a yacht,

18:29.132 --> 18:31.333
Stranded in
the middle of the ocean

18:31.401 --> 18:36.171
With no lifejackets
and no idea how to sail.

18:36.239 --> 18:39.174
Bugs! Porky!
Wait for me!

18:39.242 --> 18:41.777
hmm.

18:41.845 --> 18:44.613
These are coming with me.

18:44.681 --> 18:47.950
Mmm. It's like being caressed
by an angel.

18:51.654 --> 18:55.724
I regret nothing!

18:55.792 --> 19:00.429
Except not buying
those life jackets!

19:01.965 --> 19:03.866
It was a dream.

19:03.933 --> 19:05.734
It was all a dream.

19:05.802 --> 19:08.904
That explains why
I was such a horrible person

19:08.972 --> 19:11.273
And did
all those horrible things.

19:11.341 --> 19:13.575
Ehh...Not a dream.

19:13.643 --> 19:15.277
You are a horrible person,

19:15.345 --> 19:17.312
And you did do
those horrible things.

19:17.380 --> 19:19.047
Then what happened?

19:19.115 --> 19:20.782
- We were picked up
by a passing ship.

19:20.850 --> 19:23.252
You nearly drowned
in your stupid bedsheets.

19:23.319 --> 19:25.821
- What about "The Queen of
the Ocean"? Did she survive?

19:25.889 --> 19:28.056
- Yeah.
It was towed back to shore.

19:28.124 --> 19:30.759
oh, thank goodness!

19:30.827 --> 19:34.863
It is things that matter!
This proves it!

19:34.931 --> 19:37.232
- We sold it
and got Porky's money back.

19:37.300 --> 19:39.268
Ohh!

19:39.335 --> 19:42.037
- I have good news
and bad news.

19:42.105 --> 19:46.508
The good news is there's no
complications from the near drowning.

19:46.576 --> 19:49.244
The bad news is
we ran some tests,

19:49.312 --> 19:52.948
And it looks like
you're going to need...

19:53.016 --> 19:55.150
A kidney transplant.

19:55.218 --> 19:58.754
- Huh. Ironic. How much
does one of those cost?

19:58.821 --> 20:02.324
I don't know.
About $375,000.

20:02.392 --> 20:04.793
But I'm sure
you have insurance.

20:10.133 --> 20:12.267
Well, I may not have
insurance,

20:12.335 --> 20:14.903
But at least
I have a best friend.

20:17.573 --> 20:20.142
Right, Bugs and/or Porky?

20:26.082 --> 20:28.817
- I see you've decided
to rebuild your parade float.

20:28.885 --> 20:31.653
- Well, I couldn't ask
my best friend to do it,

20:31.721 --> 20:33.922
Not after you paid
for my kidney transplant.

20:33.990 --> 20:36.091
Don't mention it.

20:36.159 --> 20:39.628
Shame they couldn't also
throw in a brain transplant.

20:39.696 --> 20:41.029
I won't forget this!

20:41.097 --> 20:43.598
It was a tremendous act
of generosity,

20:43.666 --> 20:45.767
And I shall forever be
in your debt.

20:45.835 --> 20:47.936
- uh, Daffy,
can I take a break?

20:48.004 --> 20:50.939
I'm still not feeling 100%
since the surgery.

20:51.007 --> 20:53.208
Oh, here we go.

20:53.276 --> 20:56.445
How many times are you going
to throw it in my face

20:56.512 --> 20:58.880
That you gave me
your kidney?

20:58.948 --> 21:01.183
You still have
the other one!

21:01.250 --> 21:03.418
- I got to get
a new best friend.

